obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (47145)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Executors may sue and be sued in certain cases for wrongs committed in lifetime of deceased.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_185512_1523265304472&sectionId=47145&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_185512_1523265304472
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `An action may be maintained by the executors, administrators or representatives of any person deceased, for any wrong committed in the time of such person, which has occasioned`
  line `pecuniary loss to his estate, for which wrong an action might have been maintained by such person, so as`
  line `such wrong shall have been committed within one year before his death ^1***; and the damages, when`
  line `recovered, shall be part of the personal estate of such person;`
  line
  line `and further, an action may be maintained against the executors or administrators or heirs or`
  line `representatives of any person deceased for any wrong committed by him in his lifetime for which he`
  line `would have been subject to an action, so as such wrong shall have been committed within one year before`
  line `such person's death ^2*** and the damages to be recovered in such action shall, if recovered against an`
  line `executor or administrator bound to administer according to the English law, be payable in like order of`
  line `administration as the simple contract debts of such person.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of Central Act XII of 1855.--Section 1 of the Legal Representatives’ Suits Act,`
  line `1855 (Central Act XII of 1855) shall be renumbered as section 1A and before the section 1A`
  line `as so renumbered, the following section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `“1. Short title and extent.--This Act may be called the Legal Representatives’ Suits Act,`
  line 1855.
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of the State of Karnataka”.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka 33 of 1978, s. 4].`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "and provided such action shall be brought within one year after the death of such person" rep. by Act 9 of 1871,`
  line `s. 2 and the First Schedule, see now the Indian Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963).`
  line
  line `2. The words "and so as such action shall be commenced within two years after the committing of the wrong" rep. by s. 2 and`
  line `the First Schedule, ibid, see now Act 36 of 1963.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (47146)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Death of either party not to abate suit. Proviso.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_185512_1523265304472&sectionId=47146&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00030_185512_1523265304472
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `No action commenced under the provisions of`
  line `this Act shall abate by reason of the death of either party, but the same may be continued by or against the`
  line `executors, administrators or representatives of the party deceased: Provided that, in any case in which any`
  line `such action shall be continued against the executors, administrators or representatives of a deceased party,`
  line `such executors, administrators or representatives may set up a want of assets as a defence to the action,`
  line `either wholly or in part, in the same manner as if the action had been originally commenced against them.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
